Field coupling (interaction between fields)

B←B+κ⋅A⋅(1−B)
B←B+κ⋅A⋅(1−B)

Represents one field influencing another without breaking the core law.

Parameters (tuning knobs, domain-specific)

τ_ρ, τ_E, τ_F → time constants for responsiveness

M → stiffness / resistance to change

δ₁, δ₂ → coupling strength for excitation and inhibition

κ → cross-field interaction strength
